MASERU - Lesotho s Prime Minister Pakalitha Mosisidi has stepped down after losing in the elections. In a statement, the government says King Letsie the Third has accepted his resignation.READ: Observers dub Lesotho polls 'largely peaceful'Mosisidi will remain in his post until the new prime minister s been sworn-in.His successor is former prime minister Tom Thabane. Thabane fled Lesotho in 2014 out of concerns that there were plans to assassinate him.His party won 48 out of 120 seats - it's expected to form a governing coalition with smaller parties. eNCA